WEBVTT

00:00:15.100 --> 00:00:16.380
I must strike a deal with Sun.

00:00:16.771 --> 00:00:18.580
What leverage are you going to use
to make them comply? a deal with Sun.

00:00:18.780 --> 00:00:21.220
I’ll try talking to him first.
If that doesn’t work, we can reconsider.

00:00:21.380 --> 00:00:24.500
I’ve been using it for twenty years;
it’s just not legal in Thailand yet.

00:00:24.590 --> 00:00:27.260
My nephew will be investigated
through legal procedure.

00:00:27.540 --> 00:00:28.940
At that time, I was under
the influence of medication.

00:00:29.650 --> 00:00:31.100
So I chose Kamnan Tong.

00:00:31.410 --> 00:00:33.660
I'm afraid I might end up
causing my own father’s death.

00:00:33.770 --> 00:00:35.020
Mr. Tee has new evidence.

00:00:35.180 --> 00:00:36.620
There are records indicating
that Dr. Nong has shown...

00:00:36.740 --> 00:00:39.060
signs of confusion
and absent-mindedness.

00:00:39.260 --> 00:00:40.820
This is very significant.

00:00:40.980 --> 00:00:44.460
It will be relevant in the upcoming
debate of no-confidence.

00:00:44.740 --> 00:00:46.100
The current government has failed

00:00:46.310 --> 00:00:49.340
to uphold the promises it
made to the people.

00:00:49.540 --> 00:00:53.420
Moreover, it enabled influential groups
to build unchecked power,

00:00:53.620 --> 00:00:56.900
fueling widespread corruption
in the bureaucracy.

00:00:57.110 --> 00:01:02.220
The opposition parties have therefore
invoked Section 151 of the Constitution,

00:01:02.380 --> 00:01:07.860
submitting a motion of no-confidence
targeting seven individual ministers.

00:01:10.220 --> 00:01:14.380
Firstly, Mr. Khunwut Terdsaksakul.

00:01:14.620 --> 00:01:16.820
For failed governance,

00:01:17.060 --> 00:01:19.180
lack of integrity and moral conscience,

00:01:19.300 --> 00:01:24.580
and exploitation of the
Tele-Doctor program for personal gain.

00:01:27.060 --> 00:01:30.500
About the bidding,
I’ve settled it with Med Tech and O.P.M.,

00:01:30.740 --> 00:01:33.020
so there’s no way
any insider info leaks to Trirat.

00:01:33.210 --> 00:01:34.460
During the debate,

00:01:34.740 --> 00:01:37.900
you just need to present
the evidence for both phases.

00:01:38.180 --> 00:01:40.420
It’ll look like a fair
and tight competition to the public.

00:01:40.570 --> 00:01:41.860
No hint of collusion.

00:01:43.410 --> 00:01:46.740
Then go tweak the spec details
for each company.

00:01:47.060 --> 00:01:48.940
Check which parts give an edge
or disadvantage.

00:01:49.140 --> 00:01:50.100
Make it look smooth.

00:01:50.370 --> 00:01:51.140
Understood.

00:01:51.930 --> 00:01:57.820
Next, Dr. Thanit Phonthongdee,
Minister of Public Health.

00:01:58.160 --> 00:02:01.820
For alleged corruption tied to
the Tele-Doctor program,

00:02:02.060 --> 00:02:04.380
violations of the code of ethics,

00:02:04.620 --> 00:02:06.620
narcotics involvement,

00:02:06.830 --> 00:02:09.180
and filing falsified documents
with the court.

00:02:10.020 --> 00:02:11.580
So, is it true?

00:02:14.580 --> 00:02:16.380
The evidence that Tee presented is fake.

00:02:16.480 --> 00:02:19.260
I wasn’t asking you.
And I’m asking,

00:02:19.460 --> 00:02:21.220
is it true or not?

00:02:26.740 --> 00:02:28.420
I messed up back then.

00:02:29.660 --> 00:02:31.540
And yes, Chief Tong really died
because of it.

00:02:33.080 --> 00:02:37.540
But like Vee said,
the evidence Tee showed is fake.

00:02:38.200 --> 00:02:42.900
And that day, the nurse didn’t record
the mistake in the report either.

00:02:43.060 --> 00:02:46.620
So, can you make this issue
disappear once and for all?

00:02:47.460 --> 00:02:48.460
Yes, sir.

00:02:48.890 --> 00:02:50.940
Then, in this no-confidence debate,

00:02:51.240 --> 00:02:54.660
we should be able to get through it
without raising public suspicion.

00:02:55.320 --> 00:02:58.300
I want everyone to go back
and tell the MPs in their own factions

00:02:58.910 --> 00:03:02.940
that getting into power wasn’t easy.

00:03:03.540 --> 00:03:06.580
So don’t let anyone
make headlines again, ever.

00:04:03.420 --> 00:04:08.100
Let me be clear, the surgical record
Mr. Kosum, also known as Tee,

00:04:08.580 --> 00:04:10.020
presented as genuine is,

00:04:10.780 --> 00:04:13.620
in fact, a fake
and fabricated document.

00:04:16.270 --> 00:04:19.700
The nurse who actually recorded
the operation that day...

00:04:21.140 --> 00:04:22.140
is this person.

00:04:26.260 --> 00:04:27.100
Please, come in.

00:04:30.860 --> 00:04:32.140
This is Maifah,

00:04:32.740 --> 00:04:35.380
the nurse who recorded
the procedure that day.

00:04:36.260 --> 00:04:39.180
I’ll let her explain
what really happened.

00:04:39.640 --> 00:04:40.420
Yes.

00:04:41.140 --> 00:04:43.860
This was sabotage.

00:04:45.620 --> 00:04:48.700
What happened in the operating room
that day was…

00:05:01.100 --> 00:05:05.900
I stand by what I testified in court.

00:05:07.660 --> 00:05:10.140
It was an unforeseen incident.

00:05:14.620 --> 00:05:16.420
Dr. Nong did everything he could.

00:05:23.760 --> 00:05:25.340
You did great.

00:05:26.610 --> 00:05:28.620
Leave the rest to us.

00:05:30.410 --> 00:05:33.020
I said what you told me to say.

00:05:33.780 --> 00:05:35.700
I won’t go to jail, right?

00:05:37.070 --> 00:05:39.180
I won’t let anything happen to you.

00:05:40.900 --> 00:05:41.940
Thank you.

00:05:44.300 --> 00:05:47.100
Maifah was your witness at trial, correct?

00:05:48.100 --> 00:05:49.020
That’s right.

00:05:49.870 --> 00:05:53.180
Then she’d have to stand by
her testimony that you’re innocent.

00:05:54.330 --> 00:05:58.420
Otherwise, what she said in court
would amount to perjury,

00:05:58.660 --> 00:05:59.700
wouldn’t it?

00:06:00.020 --> 00:06:04.100
Is that true? Or is it not?

00:06:05.310 --> 00:06:08.180
The court questioned us...

00:06:09.180 --> 00:06:11.580
and ruled that both
Maifah and I told the truth.

00:06:13.120 --> 00:06:15.100
As for this so-called new evidence,

00:06:16.010 --> 00:06:18.380
it hasn’t been verified as authentic.

00:06:19.290 --> 00:06:21.620
So there will be no retrial.

00:06:22.780 --> 00:06:27.380
For the time being, I’d like to ask everyone
to respect the court’s verdict.

00:06:32.480 --> 00:06:34.100
If Nong makes a statement like that

00:06:35.260 --> 00:06:36.740
and we don’t move fast,

00:06:37.100 --> 00:06:38.580
he’s going to walk for sure.

00:06:39.500 --> 00:06:43.060
As long as we can’t prove
the surgical record is fake,

00:06:43.590 --> 00:06:45.660
we can’t flat-out call Dr. Nong guilty either.

00:06:45.800 --> 00:06:48.100
Then make it real, fast.

00:06:49.060 --> 00:06:50.780
Get that bastard Nong thrown in jail.

00:06:51.980 --> 00:06:52.940
It is fake.

00:06:53.190 --> 00:06:54.940
How are we supposed to claim it’s real?

00:06:55.980 --> 00:06:58.100
Do that, and Nong won’t sit still,

00:06:58.390 --> 00:07:00.140
he’ll dig hard to prove the truth.

00:07:00.850 --> 00:07:02.420
So what now?

00:07:03.210 --> 00:07:07.100
You’re the one who said
we could get him locked up.

00:07:07.460 --> 00:07:10.460
I said it would shake him. That’s all.

00:07:13.220 --> 00:07:14.860
Well, he’s clearly fine.

00:07:15.540 --> 00:07:16.980
Do something about it!

00:07:20.150 --> 00:07:21.740
You don’t get it.

00:07:22.940 --> 00:07:25.540
Just stay out of this.

00:07:26.100 --> 00:07:27.660
I’ll handle the rest.

00:07:29.170 --> 00:07:31.020
This isn’t what we agreed on.

00:07:31.100 --> 00:07:34.220
Or do you want an investigation to show
the documents are forged?

00:07:35.500 --> 00:07:37.060
Then you could end up in prison

00:07:37.340 --> 00:07:40.140
for falsifying records
and filing a false report.

00:07:46.980 --> 00:07:47.940
I know all

00:07:50.220 --> 00:07:51.860
you care about is rattling him.

00:07:54.420 --> 00:07:55.820
But I’m begging you

00:07:57.020 --> 00:08:02.060
to bring justice for my father.

00:08:03.170 --> 00:08:04.340
I feel for you.

00:08:06.170 --> 00:08:07.660
But this is as far as it goes.

00:08:13.330 --> 00:08:14.380
Please…

00:08:18.740 --> 00:08:21.300
Get him jailed.

00:08:22.980 --> 00:08:27.460
You’d get rid of him

00:08:28.620 --> 00:08:30.300
and free up the post, too.

00:08:37.000 --> 00:08:38.060
Please, sir…

00:08:45.340 --> 00:08:46.420
Get out of here.

00:08:47.420 --> 00:08:49.780
Sir, I’m begging you.

00:08:50.260 --> 00:08:54.300
Please help me. Please sir.

00:08:54.860 --> 00:08:57.260
Sir, please. I’m begging you.

00:08:57.650 --> 00:09:00.340
- You have to help me. Please, sir.
- Hey!

00:09:00.520 --> 00:09:02.220
You have to help me. Sir, please help me.

00:09:02.350 --> 00:09:04.180
Let go. I said, let go!

00:09:04.530 --> 00:09:05.660
Sir, please.

00:09:06.440 --> 00:09:07.940
You have to help me.

00:09:08.660 --> 00:09:10.380
You’re my only hope…

00:09:10.980 --> 00:09:11.780
Sir…

00:09:13.220 --> 00:09:14.180
Sir…

00:09:17.030 --> 00:09:20.540
For this no-confidence debate,
just go through the motions.

00:09:20.860 --> 00:09:23.540
Think of it as sharpening our game
against the opposition.

00:09:24.410 --> 00:09:25.940
Still feels pretty heavy, though.

00:09:27.110 --> 00:09:29.900
Exactly, sir. The situation with Dr. Nong
still isn’t resolved.

00:09:32.010 --> 00:09:35.100
Sun says he’ll sort it out quickly…

00:09:36.260 --> 00:09:37.140
isn’t that right?

00:09:38.340 --> 00:09:39.140
Of course.

00:09:40.060 --> 00:09:42.060
We’re all on the same team here.

00:09:43.260 --> 00:09:45.340
Or is someone
having a problem with that?

00:09:46.580 --> 00:09:48.580
Just grumbling a little.

00:09:48.950 --> 00:09:51.340
Whatever the main party decides,
we’ll follow.

00:09:53.210 --> 00:09:56.620
Hearing that from you
eases my mind.

00:09:57.860 --> 00:10:02.660
So what, everything I said before
carried no weight?

00:10:03.700 --> 00:10:04.740
No, sir.

00:10:04.900 --> 00:10:09.380
I know you want a cabinet reshuffle.

00:10:10.580 --> 00:10:12.780
Should I do it
without your party in the room?

00:10:12.910 --> 00:10:15.820
Oh, no, it’s not that serious, sir.

00:10:18.420 --> 00:10:20.420
If anyone has doubts or issues,
say it here and now.

00:10:21.960 --> 00:10:23.780
Let’s clear the air.

00:10:28.350 --> 00:10:29.820
But if no one speaks up,

00:10:30.180 --> 00:10:34.220
don’t let me find out later
you’ve been talking behind my back.

00:10:41.830 --> 00:10:43.740
Out of all people,

00:10:43.930 --> 00:10:46.980
you should know just how weak
Khunawut’s government really is.

00:10:47.140 --> 00:10:50.100
Why waste your time
on a washed-up old man

00:10:50.200 --> 00:10:52.700
when you’re more than ready to step up?

00:10:53.850 --> 00:10:58.220
Let’s not make the people wait
any longer for our government.

00:10:58.420 --> 00:11:03.300
I want to work,
I don’t want to be Prime Minister.

00:11:13.400 --> 00:11:19.380
How long has it been since we Phu Chalerm
folks were all together like this?

00:11:24.750 --> 00:11:28.380
Didn’t you say you had something
to discuss with Dr. Nong, Nath?

00:11:29.000 --> 00:11:31.540
I don’t think I’ve got anything
to say to the Minister.

00:11:31.820 --> 00:11:36.900
No one wants to talk to
a scandal-ridden minister like me, Supa.

00:11:37.320 --> 00:11:39.420
Oh, Dr. Nong…

00:11:40.260 --> 00:11:44.620
Only people who’ve never done anything
have never made mistakes.

00:11:46.860 --> 00:11:49.180
Don’t worry about
the censure debate,

00:11:49.330 --> 00:11:50.740
you’ll get through it for sure.

00:11:51.020 --> 00:11:52.860
It’s not going to be that easy, Supa.

00:11:54.780 --> 00:11:57.620
If it were, Vee wouldn’t be
calling strategy meetings like this.

00:12:02.750 --> 00:12:05.140
Khim, may I speak with you?

00:12:05.500 --> 00:12:07.220
- Uh, well…
- Right now.

00:12:18.370 --> 00:12:21.220
What’s going on, Ni?
Why does it seem so serious?

00:12:22.660 --> 00:12:24.420
We’ve found a Turncoat.

00:12:26.820 --> 00:12:28.940
Come on… Khim? Really?

00:12:29.410 --> 00:12:33.340
Yes. We just haven’t
caught her red-handed yet.

00:12:33.600 --> 00:12:37.060
Vee’s just going to tell her
we suspect her.

00:12:37.340 --> 00:12:38.700
If we’re not wrong,

00:12:38.890 --> 00:12:43.260
we’ll soon see
who she’s been talking to.

00:12:43.810 --> 00:12:45.740
And from there, we’ll track down

00:12:45.980 --> 00:12:48.220
who else they’ve tried to buy.

00:12:48.320 --> 00:12:50.300
Oh my gosh,
there’s more of them!?

00:12:58.990 --> 00:13:02.580
Okay. See you in half an hour.
I’ll be careful.

00:13:33.240 --> 00:13:35.220
You said you had something
important to warn me about…

00:13:35.690 --> 00:13:37.660
So I thought
I should bring Vee along too.

00:13:37.790 --> 00:13:39.180
Hope that’s okay.

00:13:41.280 --> 00:13:45.100
I’m a little disappointed
to find out it’s you.

00:13:54.180 --> 00:13:55.500
What the hell did you do, Nath?

00:13:56.890 --> 00:13:58.900
You seriously pulled this stunt without
thinking about how it reflects on me?

00:14:00.060 --> 00:14:01.380
You betrayed the party,

00:14:02.660 --> 00:14:05.700
and you were dumb enough to fall
into their trap, too?

00:14:06.770 --> 00:14:07.980
Tell me right now.

00:14:09.420 --> 00:14:11.060
You haven’t taken their money yet, right?

00:14:12.060 --> 00:14:13.740
If you haven’t, I can go tell Vee,

00:14:14.060 --> 00:14:16.380
and we’ll tell the party they approached you,
but you turned them down.

00:14:22.580 --> 00:14:23.820
Answer me, damn it, Nath.

00:14:23.910 --> 00:14:26.260
- I’m trying to help you here!
- Help me?

00:14:28.410 --> 00:14:31.660
You’re just scared you’ll get hit
in the no-confidence debate.

00:14:33.650 --> 00:14:36.180
You’re a turncoat.
They’ll crush you for it.

00:14:36.720 --> 00:14:38.100
That’s why I’m talking to you.

00:14:38.240 --> 00:14:39.740
You think I’m doing this for myself?

00:14:43.390 --> 00:14:45.180
You haven’t taken their money yet, right?

00:14:46.940 --> 00:14:47.740
Not yet.

00:14:48.240 --> 00:14:51.980
Good. Go tell them you’re out.

00:15:00.600 --> 00:15:01.700
I’m taking the money.

00:15:09.340 --> 00:15:12.660
How much did they pay you, Nath?
How much to sell yourself like that?

00:15:13.260 --> 00:15:15.180
Enough for me to finally get my work done.

00:15:15.280 --> 00:15:17.500
There are other ways to get work done.

00:15:17.580 --> 00:15:19.860
I’m just doing exactly
what you told me to.

00:15:20.540 --> 00:15:22.660
Do whatever it takes to get the job done.

00:15:23.060 --> 00:15:25.140
This just happens
to be the method you don’t like.

00:15:33.990 --> 00:15:35.420
I’m here talking to you

00:15:35.630 --> 00:15:38.060
because I care about you
and I want to help.

00:15:38.770 --> 00:15:39.900
You’re like a brother to me.

00:15:40.000 --> 00:15:41.380
Otherwise,
I would’ve let Vee take care of this.

00:15:41.500 --> 00:15:44.900
Before you try to help me,
save yourself first.

00:15:45.700 --> 00:15:46.300
Nath

00:15:46.410 --> 00:15:48.020
You called me brother just because

00:15:48.250 --> 00:15:50.860
you want to be another dirty politician.

00:15:51.300 --> 00:15:53.140
If I stay with you as ‘brother’ any longer,

00:15:53.330 --> 00:15:55.940
I’ll end up in prison for you,
just like Jump did.

00:16:15.170 --> 00:16:16.060
Hello?

00:16:16.830 --> 00:16:18.460
I’ve got something to report.

00:16:18.930 --> 00:16:20.900
But this time, it’s not about drugs,

00:16:21.620 --> 00:16:23.380
it’s something even bigger.

00:16:23.700 --> 00:16:26.820
Could I get a little more bonus
for this one?

00:16:28.400 --> 00:16:29.820
What Dr. Nong did was wrong,

00:16:30.300 --> 00:16:31.780
but you’re the one who crossed the line.

00:16:32.680 --> 00:16:34.860
I wish none of this had ever happened,

00:16:36.420 --> 00:16:37.620
the thing with Dr. Nong,

00:16:39.120 --> 00:16:40.860
and you turning into a turncoat.

00:16:44.940 --> 00:16:46.260
You don’t have to sweet-talk me.

00:16:48.420 --> 00:16:49.620
I’ve made my decision.

00:16:53.350 --> 00:16:55.260
I’ve lost faith in your party.

00:16:56.490 --> 00:16:57.700
Just let me go.

00:16:59.580 --> 00:17:01.340
I can’t afford to lose
even a single vote.

00:17:02.380 --> 00:17:04.420
Dr. Nong’s situation
is already hanging by a thread.

00:17:07.100 --> 00:17:08.620
I’ve made my choice.

00:17:15.120 --> 00:17:17.140
If I can’t persuade you…

00:17:27.420 --> 00:17:29.020
I’m just doing my job.

00:17:29.950 --> 00:17:34.060
Anyone joining our team
has to be vetted.

00:17:36.150 --> 00:17:39.700
Back when you took that
sponsorship deal,

00:17:40.460 --> 00:17:41.980
you probably didn’t know, right?

00:17:42.660 --> 00:17:45.620
That it was money laundered
from an online gambling ring.

00:17:47.100 --> 00:17:49.100
But if you don’t want to
explain that to the police,

00:17:49.410 --> 00:17:50.460
then here’s the trade

00:17:50.820 --> 00:17:52.100
You stay quiet about Dr. Nong,

00:17:53.650 --> 00:17:55.100
and I’ll keep my mouth
shut about you.

00:18:04.530 --> 00:18:06.380
Oh, and during the debate,

00:18:09.610 --> 00:18:11.020
stay in line.

00:18:24.610 --> 00:18:26.700
Here’s compensation for your time.

00:18:27.200 --> 00:18:28.140
Thank you, sir.

00:18:29.580 --> 00:18:32.900
So there are no backups
of the footage anywhere else?

00:18:33.620 --> 00:18:34.580
There’s nothing else, sir.

00:18:35.850 --> 00:18:39.140
No one can know about this.
Not even people at the party.

00:18:39.290 --> 00:18:40.060
Understood.

00:18:48.180 --> 00:18:49.620
Gale, we got it.

00:18:50.410 --> 00:18:52.340
That security guy
charged us a fortune.

00:18:52.740 --> 00:18:55.660
If there’s nothing shady
about the doctor in here,

00:18:55.980 --> 00:18:56.980
it’s gonna be such a letdown.

00:18:57.190 --> 00:18:58.780
Don’t be let down.

00:18:59.460 --> 00:19:01.700
If there is something,
it’s good for the story.

00:19:02.180 --> 00:19:04.020
If there’s nothing,
it’s good for the people.

00:19:04.330 --> 00:19:05.020
Right?

00:19:05.150 --> 00:19:08.780
Yeah, but not good for us.
That’s what we call a loss.

00:19:14.700 --> 00:19:17.340
Congrats then, no loss here.

00:19:21.410 --> 00:19:24.140
You don’t give us a break
with your scandals, don’t you, doc?

00:19:34.690 --> 00:19:36.300
It’s been a while, hasn’t it,
Mr. Phasakorn?

00:19:36.920 --> 00:19:37.620
Yes,

00:19:38.100 --> 00:19:40.620
I believe the last time
was during the debate?

00:19:43.940 --> 00:19:44.740
That’s right.

00:19:45.660 --> 00:19:46.740
Funny, isn’t it?

00:19:47.700 --> 00:19:49.620
Back then, we were rivals,

00:19:50.500 --> 00:19:52.780
and now we’re in the same Cabinet.

00:19:53.430 --> 00:19:54.860
And yet, still competing.

00:19:58.090 --> 00:20:00.300
Who am I to compete
with the party leader?

00:20:01.780 --> 00:20:03.340
I meant in terms of performance.

00:20:04.120 --> 00:20:07.100
The first phase of your
Tele-Doctor Project is going pretty well.

00:20:07.250 --> 00:20:08.220
I’ve been following it.

00:20:09.850 --> 00:20:10.780
Thanks.

00:20:11.820 --> 00:20:14.460
Honestly, working with Dr. Chalong
was actually fun.

00:20:15.890 --> 00:20:18.340
But I doubt phase two
will be as fun for him

00:20:19.240 --> 00:20:21.420
since the suppliers changed
from Med Tech to O.P.M.

00:20:23.220 --> 00:20:27.420
Hmm… But is that
a good thing for you?

00:20:28.380 --> 00:20:32.300
When you get grilled in the debate,
you can point out that you changed suppliers

00:20:32.620 --> 00:20:34.620
to avoid favoritism.

00:20:36.900 --> 00:20:39.260
Well, we don’t even need
to say that, right?

00:20:40.020 --> 00:20:42.020
Because the bidding process
in our country

00:20:43.300 --> 00:20:45.140
is squeaky clean, isn’t it?

00:20:45.700 --> 00:20:46.660
Exactly.

00:20:51.200 --> 00:20:52.860
why the sudden spec change...

00:20:54.620 --> 00:20:56.900
for Phase Two?

00:20:57.720 --> 00:21:00.660
Med Tech was getting the benefits,

00:21:01.370 --> 00:21:05.540
why surrender them
and switch to O.P.M.?

00:21:07.080 --> 00:21:10.500
Doctor, you haven’t heard?

00:21:11.810 --> 00:21:16.700
So your other half mentioned
it needed a special backroom deal,

00:21:18.860 --> 00:21:19.980
has he?

00:21:27.380 --> 00:21:28.660
What do you mean?

00:21:33.930 --> 00:21:38.300
Well, if Vee hadn’t stayed up
all night talking to me,

00:21:39.460 --> 00:21:41.300
this wouldn’t have gone
through so smoothly.

00:22:10.500 --> 00:22:14.620
How about a little trip down
memory lane?

00:23:13.010 --> 00:23:14.220
Where’d you go with Sun?

00:23:20.200 --> 00:23:21.500
Did you sleep with him?

00:23:22.000 --> 00:23:23.140
Where the hell is this coming from?

00:23:24.940 --> 00:23:26.180
So it’s true, isn’t it?

00:23:27.240 --> 00:23:30.100
Are you insane?
I didn’t do anything!

00:23:31.060 --> 00:23:33.900
You really think I’d sleep with Sun?

00:23:35.200 --> 00:23:36.540
Then tell me,

00:23:37.420 --> 00:23:39.260
why the hell would he give up
the upper hand

00:23:39.580 --> 00:23:42.100
and hand your dad hundreds of millions
from a rigged bid, just like that?

00:23:45.080 --> 00:23:47.620
He just wanted to help me.
That’s all.

00:23:48.780 --> 00:23:50.580
You’re not even good at lying anymore.

00:23:51.210 --> 00:23:52.860
That’s the best excuse you’ve got?

00:23:53.300 --> 00:23:54.900
What the hell is wrong with you?

00:23:55.260 --> 00:23:57.020
We’ve been through so much crap

00:23:57.730 --> 00:24:00.740
that we’re way past sitting
around worrying about lies, aren’t we?

00:24:00.860 --> 00:24:02.020
Don’t touch me.

00:24:04.060 --> 00:24:05.660
Because I never doubted you.

00:24:06.620 --> 00:24:08.340
Not at all.

00:24:09.060 --> 00:24:11.020
So that’s why you keep
stringing me along.

00:24:12.500 --> 00:24:15.180
When I’m telling the truth,
you won't believe me.

00:24:15.710 --> 00:24:17.180
What the hell am I supposed to do?

00:24:17.300 --> 00:24:20.780
If it were you, would you believe it?

00:24:21.290 --> 00:24:22.460
Would you buy that?

00:24:22.610 --> 00:24:25.020
Sun tossed away hundreds
of millions after one talk?

00:24:25.320 --> 00:24:26.300
You really think so?

00:24:26.420 --> 00:24:30.740
Tell me, is there anything
you’ve said to me that’s real?

00:24:30.970 --> 00:24:33.300
You haven’t even given me
the chance to explain!

00:24:33.400 --> 00:24:34.100
Enough.

00:24:35.850 --> 00:24:37.700
I don’t want to hear any more
of your lies.

00:24:37.950 --> 00:24:39.660
- What the hell is wrong with you?
- Stay away from me.

00:24:39.890 --> 00:24:40.940
Come on, Doc.

00:24:41.610 --> 00:24:42.420
Doc.

00:24:44.780 --> 00:24:45.740
Get out.

00:24:47.570 --> 00:24:48.980
Don’t let me see your face again.

00:24:56.940 --> 00:24:57.740
Get out.

00:24:59.860 --> 00:25:00.780
Get out!

00:25:47.310 --> 00:25:51.460
This no-confidence debate is one to watch,

00:25:51.650 --> 00:25:53.800
with issues including alleged favoritism,

00:25:53.900 --> 00:25:56.940
narcotics,
and the case involving Chief Tong.

00:25:57.090 --> 00:26:01.180
Dr. Nong, which issue
is your greatest concern?

00:26:01.860 --> 00:26:03.060
Honestly…

00:26:03.890 --> 00:26:05.100
none of them.

00:26:06.950 --> 00:26:09.580
Because I didn’t do anything wrong.

00:26:11.010 --> 00:26:14.300
Still as direct
and composed as always.

00:26:15.010 --> 00:26:16.340
Let me put it this way:

00:26:17.810 --> 00:26:19.300
I’m here to work,

00:26:20.660 --> 00:26:23.740
not play politics.

00:26:26.580 --> 00:26:29.540
If people out there say
I’m doing a bad job,

00:26:30.300 --> 00:26:35.140
that hurts more than anything
the opposition can accuse me of.

00:26:35.660 --> 00:26:39.820
So, you’re fully prepared for the debate?

00:26:40.060 --> 00:26:41.980
I’m ready

00:26:42.300 --> 00:26:43.540
hands, feet, whatever comes.

00:26:43.700 --> 00:26:46.340
Wow, you’re in great spirits.

00:26:46.440 --> 00:26:49.580
So, would you mind
if I move to a lighter question?

00:26:50.040 --> 00:26:50.860
Go ahead.

00:26:51.610 --> 00:26:53.900
Well, I’ve noticed from the monitor

00:26:54.180 --> 00:26:56.500
that you’ve got a photo of you
and MP Withu displayed in your office.

00:26:56.680 --> 00:27:00.460
Is that to serve the fans?

00:27:15.500 --> 00:27:16.540
Apologies,

00:27:16.930 --> 00:27:24.020
but I think it’s about time we all stop
paying attention to this ‘ship.’

00:27:28.960 --> 00:27:31.180
I’d rather have people focus on my work

00:27:31.420 --> 00:27:34.220
and whether I’ve delivered on
what I promised during the campaign.

00:27:35.320 --> 00:27:38.340
Not this narrative that was spun...

00:27:41.250 --> 00:27:42.740
and built up by someone else.

00:27:43.900 --> 00:27:45.740
by someone else.

00:27:48.080 --> 00:27:53.180
Let me be perfectly clear,
for the last time,

00:27:53.890 --> 00:27:55.580
that MP Withu and I...

00:27:58.170 --> 00:28:03.100
are simply party colleagues.

00:28:06.340 --> 00:28:07.780
We work together

00:28:11.660 --> 00:28:14.260
and there's nothing more.

00:29:06.940 --> 00:29:08.660
Aren’t you happy I came to visit?

00:29:21.010 --> 00:29:22.500
Over the moon.

00:29:27.470 --> 00:29:30.900
But I just don’t want you
to see me like this.

00:29:37.770 --> 00:29:39.140
Look at me.

00:29:43.660 --> 00:29:45.260
From where I’m standing,

00:29:46.420 --> 00:29:48.180
you’ve never looked cooler.

00:29:50.970 --> 00:29:52.860
You don’t have to say it
to cheer me up.

00:29:55.560 --> 00:29:57.140
At the end of the day,

00:29:59.420 --> 00:30:00.940
I’m just some ex-con now.

00:30:05.600 --> 00:30:09.220
You talk like I don’t know
you went to jail to protect Dr. Nong.

00:30:15.180 --> 00:30:16.980
But no one else knows that.

00:30:18.300 --> 00:30:19.340
Honestly?

00:30:20.930 --> 00:30:23.980
I’m scared no one will ever know the truth.

00:30:25.070 --> 00:30:27.980
And I’m scared that one day,

00:30:29.340 --> 00:30:31.460
I’ll realize that I shouldn’t have gone
along with the plan.

00:30:40.180 --> 00:30:41.580
I’m sorry, Jump.

00:30:45.800 --> 00:30:47.180
Why are you apologizing?

00:30:48.850 --> 00:30:50.500
You didn’t do anything wrong.

00:30:51.260 --> 00:30:52.460
And don’t worry,

00:30:53.580 --> 00:30:55.660
I could never be mad
at our Boss or Vee.

00:30:56.580 --> 00:30:57.620
Don’t worry about it.

00:31:07.200 --> 00:31:08.020
See?

00:31:08.760 --> 00:31:11.060
That’s why I said
you look even cooler now.

00:31:12.810 --> 00:31:14.020
Don’t worry.

00:31:14.500 --> 00:31:17.860
No matter what people say,
when you get out,

00:31:18.730 --> 00:31:21.260
I won’t be ashamed to walk beside you.

00:31:23.050 --> 00:31:24.780
Are you giving me hope?

00:31:25.960 --> 00:31:26.940
Yeah.

00:31:29.120 --> 00:31:32.740
I always want the best for you.

00:31:37.810 --> 00:31:39.260
Damn, that was kind of touching.

00:31:42.340 --> 00:31:43.620
Stay strong.

00:31:44.620 --> 00:31:47.340
Vee and I are trying
to find a way to get you out.

00:31:50.590 --> 00:31:51.980
But right now

00:31:55.220 --> 00:31:56.780
our team’s not the same anymore.

00:33:09.420 --> 00:33:13.900
This CCTV footage shows
MP Nath of the Vivat Siam Party,

00:33:14.040 --> 00:33:15.620
who suffered a head injury

00:33:15.740 --> 00:33:19.780
and was rushed to the hospital
by fellow party member MP Withu.

00:33:19.940 --> 00:33:21.900
Twenty minutes prior,

00:33:22.060 --> 00:33:26.060
Dr. Nong had entered the room and remained
with MP Nath for nearly ten minutes.

00:33:26.250 --> 00:33:27.940
What really happened inside that room?

00:33:28.100 --> 00:33:32.500
And beyond that,
what has Dr. Nong done up to now?

00:33:32.690 --> 00:33:36.260
Be it the narcotics issue
or the case of Chief Tong?

00:33:36.540 --> 00:33:39.820
What is the truth?
This can’t go unanswered.

00:33:59.530 --> 00:34:00.860
Vee asked me to tell you this:

00:34:01.220 --> 00:34:04.420
if you’re going to lie low,
then lie low from everyone.

00:34:04.990 --> 00:34:06.660
Keep your head down, stay quiet,

00:34:07.330 --> 00:34:09.140
and wait for things to settle.

00:34:09.930 --> 00:34:10.900
That’s it.

00:34:18.450 --> 00:34:19.380
Doc,

00:34:20.780 --> 00:34:24.700
I think you’ve taken it too far
by shutting Vee out on purpose like this.

00:34:25.980 --> 00:34:27.100
He knows what’s going on,

00:34:29.610 --> 00:34:31.820
and he’s still fighting for you.

00:34:33.810 --> 00:34:35.100
Please,

00:34:36.560 --> 00:34:38.180
you have to start listening to him.

00:34:39.810 --> 00:34:41.300
You’re not in this alone.

00:34:45.100 --> 00:34:47.220
You’re carrying all of our hopes.

00:34:58.680 --> 00:35:01.180
That day, Dr. Nong
came to talk to me as usual.

00:35:02.740 --> 00:35:04.980
But we had some disagreement.

00:35:05.850 --> 00:35:08.380
I ran out to clear the air,

00:35:09.900 --> 00:35:14.220
but I tripped over a power cord
and hit my head.

00:35:18.450 --> 00:35:23.740
After Dr. Nong told MP Withu
we’d exchanged words,

00:35:24.020 --> 00:35:28.140
he came to check on me.

00:35:29.660 --> 00:35:33.300
When he walked in
and saw me unconscious,

00:35:34.150 --> 00:35:36.540
he rushed me to the hospital.

00:35:37.060 --> 00:35:38.340
That’s all there is to it.

00:35:38.490 --> 00:35:41.260
Then why isn’t Dr. Nong here today
to explain it himself?

00:35:46.420 --> 00:35:48.380
He had an urgent matter.

00:35:49.020 --> 00:35:51.420
Are you sure
everything you’ve said is true?

00:35:51.910 --> 00:35:53.940
You’re not covering for him?

00:35:59.380 --> 00:36:00.380
I stand by it.

00:36:03.810 --> 00:36:06.060
Don’t worry about Dr. Nong,
I’ve talked him down.

00:36:06.290 --> 00:36:09.910
If there’s anything urgent, call Chatch
he’s turned his phone back on.

00:36:10.500 --> 00:36:11.460
Thanks.

00:36:11.830 --> 00:36:13.620
What’s Doc even mad about?

00:36:13.930 --> 00:36:16.180
It’s just your ex still having feelings for you
what’s the big deal?

00:36:16.850 --> 00:36:18.060
You know how Sun is,

00:36:18.440 --> 00:36:20.940
he’s a pro at messing with people’s heads.

00:36:21.960 --> 00:36:24.540
And our Dr. Nong is hot-headed enough
to walk right into it.

00:36:24.840 --> 00:36:26.420
Keep an eye on him for me.

00:36:27.760 --> 00:36:30.380
There’s so much drama lately,

00:36:30.720 --> 00:36:32.020
I can barely catch my breath.

00:36:32.800 --> 00:36:34.340
Blame Sun.

00:36:35.170 --> 00:36:39.220
The whole party’s in chaos,
and he’s still stirring the pot.

00:36:42.180 --> 00:36:43.060
Shit.

00:36:44.980 --> 00:36:46.260
Why am I only seeing this now?

00:36:46.650 --> 00:36:47.900
Exactly.

00:36:48.060 --> 00:36:50.060
He’s playing hero for your dad
to rack up the points.

00:36:50.210 --> 00:36:51.180
It’s more than that.

00:36:51.440 --> 00:36:53.340
Sun didn’t back off
from the Med Tech deal

00:36:53.790 --> 00:36:55.700
just to split me and Dr. Nong up.

00:36:56.860 --> 00:36:58.540
He’s trying to bring down
the government.

00:37:00.020 --> 00:37:02.500
Wouldn’t it be easier to just abstain
in the confidence vote?

00:37:02.610 --> 00:37:03.940
Why make it complicated?

00:37:07.100 --> 00:37:08.020
Think about it,

00:37:08.200 --> 00:37:10.540
if parliament dissolves
and there’s a new election

00:37:10.780 --> 00:37:12.580
while Dr. Nong’s still clean,

00:37:12.730 --> 00:37:14.380
a political star, what happens?

00:37:14.770 --> 00:37:18.500
Nothing changes. Or worse,
Sun might have to pay more for support.

00:37:20.820 --> 00:37:21.780
Shit!

00:37:22.000 --> 00:37:24.060
Do you think the current charges
were Sun’s doing?

00:37:24.120 --> 00:37:27.700
That drug-search video leaked
from the cops to Gale?

00:37:27.840 --> 00:37:29.340
I don’t need more proof to know
who’s behind it.

00:37:29.440 --> 00:37:31.340
So now the party’s at odds with Dr. Nong,

00:37:31.450 --> 00:37:33.020
and Dr. Nong is at odds with you.

00:37:33.200 --> 00:37:34.620
Divide and conquer.

00:37:34.900 --> 00:37:37.460
If our party weakens, who benefits?

00:37:38.380 --> 00:37:39.340
Shit.

00:37:39.600 --> 00:37:40.580
And I wouldn’t be surprised

00:37:40.780 --> 00:37:44.580
if that fake Chief Tong
evidence was his, too.

00:37:44.790 --> 00:37:46.140
He orchestrated all of it?

00:37:50.460 --> 00:37:51.420
The thing is,

00:37:51.700 --> 00:37:53.700
I think the real damage
hasn’t even started.

00:38:01.520 --> 00:38:04.460
What are your thoughts on
the upcoming no-confidence debate?

00:38:05.140 --> 00:38:09.300
I see it as nothing more than
an attempt to discredit the government.

00:38:09.460 --> 00:38:12.340
But overall, we remain very stable.

00:38:12.830 --> 00:38:14.820
Given the drop in public trust,

00:38:14.930 --> 00:38:17.380
what strategy will you
and your coalition partners pursue?

00:38:17.500 --> 00:38:18.420
Rest assured,

00:38:18.610 --> 00:38:20.860
we’ll leave no room
for doubt about this government.

00:38:21.180 --> 00:38:22.860
If someone crosses the line,
we’ll take decisive action,

00:38:23.130 --> 00:38:25.460
we’ll deal with it decisively.

00:38:26.040 --> 00:38:27.660
Are you referring to Dr. Nong?

00:38:37.410 --> 00:38:39.140
Doctor, you should rest a bit.

00:38:39.380 --> 00:38:43.100
When we’re near the condo,
I’ll swing by and pick up your usual congee.

00:38:43.960 --> 00:38:45.100
Thanks, Chatch.

00:39:14.800 --> 00:39:15.980
Why are we going this way?

00:39:29.770 --> 00:39:30.380
Chatch?

00:39:31.110 --> 00:39:32.540
Hey, Chatch

00:39:32.900 --> 00:39:33.700
Chatch!

00:40:13.940 --> 00:40:15.220
Let’s talk in the car.

00:41:07.740 --> 00:41:10.980
How about
a little trip down memory lane?

00:41:20.180 --> 00:41:20.860
Okay,

00:41:24.300 --> 00:41:25.860
I wouldn’t have gone through with it,
you know.

00:41:26.830 --> 00:41:29.220
The moment you didn’t consent,
it was already over.

00:41:35.830 --> 00:41:37.380
There’s someone in your eyes.

00:41:43.810 --> 00:41:46.260
But, even if I can’t win you back,

00:41:47.660 --> 00:41:49.500
I don’t want you to hate me.

00:41:52.700 --> 00:41:54.020
Can we still be friends?

00:41:57.100 --> 00:41:58.180
Okay,

00:41:59.610 --> 00:42:03.900
I’ll sign off on switching
the Tele-Doctor supplier to O.P.M.

00:42:05.270 --> 00:42:07.780
Just don’t go around saying
I caved that easily.

00:42:08.150 --> 00:42:09.660
Let me save a little face.

00:42:11.900 --> 00:42:12.900
Thank you.

00:42:20.050 --> 00:42:23.580
About that 'trip down memory lane'...

00:42:28.860 --> 00:42:30.140
How about a game of Catan?

00:42:30.720 --> 00:42:33.380
I haven’t had anyone to play with
since I came back to the party.

00:42:38.140 --> 00:42:38.900
Come on,

00:42:40.020 --> 00:42:41.700
let’s pull an all-nighter like we used to.

00:42:43.780 --> 00:42:44.740
Please?

00:42:55.370 --> 00:42:56.260
All right then.

00:42:57.620 --> 00:42:58.900
I’ll wait.

00:43:00.470 --> 00:43:03.940
Maybe one day,
we’ll play Catan again.

00:43:10.650 --> 00:43:11.780
Don’t wait for me.

00:43:24.720 --> 00:43:27.500
You really don’t feel anything
for him anymore, do you?

00:43:30.610 --> 00:43:31.980
After everything we’ve been through,

00:43:33.020 --> 00:43:34.420
you still don’t trust me?

00:43:39.770 --> 00:43:41.100
I just...

00:43:43.660 --> 00:43:45.700
...wanted to hear it from you.

00:43:50.110 --> 00:43:51.220
Okay.

00:43:52.300 --> 00:43:54.540
I’m not going back to him,

00:43:55.740 --> 00:43:57.540
no matter how good he is to me.

00:43:58.620 --> 00:44:00.500
Whatever, I felt burned out
a long time ago.

00:44:02.460 --> 00:44:03.700
You mean it?

00:44:04.660 --> 00:44:05.540
Yeah.

00:44:11.340 --> 00:44:12.180
And...

00:44:13.620 --> 00:44:17.540
what he said about you
having someone else in your eyes…

00:44:17.860 --> 00:44:24.340
So the way you kept
pressing me and losing it,

00:44:25.460 --> 00:44:28.460
that wasn’t about me cutting
some deal on the side.

00:44:31.540 --> 00:44:33.100
It was about something else, right?

00:44:41.540 --> 00:44:43.180
How do you really feel about me?

00:44:49.770 --> 00:44:51.340
Do I still have to say it?

00:44:56.200 --> 00:44:59.620
I want to hear it from you.

00:45:01.540 --> 00:45:02.540
That’s all.

00:48:43.060 --> 00:48:44.740
You’re up?

00:48:45.020 --> 00:48:45.740
Yep.

00:48:46.820 --> 00:48:47.980
I’ll bring it over.

00:48:52.150 --> 00:48:53.500
This is for you.

00:48:53.620 --> 00:48:54.780
Thank you.

00:48:59.770 --> 00:49:01.900
- Getting back at me?
- Just a little.

00:49:11.000 --> 00:49:12.620
It’s just fried eggs and toast.

00:49:13.940 --> 00:49:19.020
Nobody was here last week,
so I didn’t stock up.

00:49:21.300 --> 00:49:23.780
Good to see you’re eating something.

00:49:24.210 --> 00:49:26.540
You’ve gotten so skinny
I can see your ribs.

00:49:28.420 --> 00:49:29.500
Was that a grope?

00:49:31.700 --> 00:49:32.660
Was that payback?

00:49:34.820 --> 00:49:35.860
Can’t help it.

00:49:36.900 --> 00:49:40.060
I don’t eat, I just drink.

00:49:40.930 --> 00:49:42.380
Too lazy to work.

00:49:42.660 --> 00:49:45.940
Body’s a mess, mind’s worse.

00:49:46.260 --> 00:49:48.100
Nobody really takes care of me.

00:49:49.860 --> 00:49:54.020
When someone did,
you kicked him out, remember?

00:49:59.030 --> 00:50:01.380
Sorry. Won’t happen again.

00:50:06.380 --> 00:50:09.580
A politician’s promise? Please.

00:50:10.480 --> 00:50:11.780
You can trust me.

00:50:15.790 --> 00:50:18.180
Tell you what, I'll resign,

00:50:18.930 --> 00:50:22.980
we’ll move back to Phu Chaloem,
and start a farm.

00:50:23.740 --> 00:50:28.380
I’ll buy twenty buffalo.
We’ll get rich raising them.

00:50:30.020 --> 00:50:31.180
You’re talking nonsense.

00:50:32.540 --> 00:50:33.820
Eat your breakfast

00:50:34.980 --> 00:50:36.180
and get to work.

00:50:36.570 --> 00:50:38.740
Your ratings are in the gutter.

00:50:39.420 --> 00:50:41.260
Time to step up, got it?

00:50:42.540 --> 00:50:43.700
My ratings went downhill?

00:50:45.220 --> 00:50:46.220
I don’t think so.

00:50:46.980 --> 00:50:50.580
Because last night,
I premiered a brand-new performance.

00:50:52.820 --> 00:50:54.260
First time, too.

00:50:55.260 --> 00:50:59.620
So I’m wondering,
was the performance satisfactory?

00:51:01.110 --> 00:51:02.540
Want to rate it?

00:51:06.540 --> 00:51:07.500
Hmm…

00:51:12.900 --> 00:51:18.180
It wasn’t exactly… clear.

00:51:18.980 --> 00:51:20.300
Not clear enough?

00:51:24.950 --> 00:51:26.260
Not clear enough?

00:51:27.240 --> 00:51:28.940
You want it clearer?

00:51:29.260 --> 00:51:29.900
Hey!

00:51:30.120 --> 00:51:31.700
You want it to be crystal clear?

00:51:31.880 --> 00:51:33.380
- Right here?
- Right here.

00:51:33.700 --> 00:51:35.020
Let’s go.

00:51:43.500 --> 00:51:44.740
This is for you.

00:51:45.970 --> 00:51:46.900
You’re here?

00:52:03.140 --> 00:52:06.580
With that goofy smile.
Did a girl send it to you?

00:52:08.960 --> 00:52:12.460
Can’t a man smile just ‘cause he’s about
to eat something delicious?

00:52:13.660 --> 00:52:14.460
Here,

00:52:15.060 --> 00:52:16.460
since you're so nosy, take one.

00:52:16.740 --> 00:52:18.300
Thanks, Doc!

00:52:18.890 --> 00:52:20.020
Now get going.

00:52:33.580 --> 00:52:34.980
Little croissant, huh?

00:52:49.090 --> 00:52:51.420
If this phase three comes in at this number,
I really can’t go through with it.

00:52:51.620 --> 00:52:54.500
Hey, why is it so hard for you
to understand?

00:52:55.820 --> 00:52:57.740
No, sir, I just want to inform you that...

00:52:57.850 --> 00:53:00.860
You want the contract, right?
Then how’s this acceptable, huh?

00:53:02.550 --> 00:53:05.980
In that case, I suggest we should propose
an amendment to the TOR.

00:53:07.860 --> 00:53:12.140
What you just heard
was a clip of a recorded call

00:53:12.540 --> 00:53:16.060
between a senior government official

00:53:17.660 --> 00:53:19.700
and a corporate representative,

00:53:20.240 --> 00:53:25.060
colluding on a state project.

00:53:25.610 --> 00:53:29.500
And here is the full transcript of that call.

00:53:29.860 --> 00:53:33.020
Both the audio and the transcript
will be presented

00:53:33.430 --> 00:53:35.980
in full during
the no-confidence debate.

00:53:37.200 --> 00:53:40.860
Now that the evidence is out,
what’s our next move?

00:53:41.220 --> 00:53:44.020
Illegally obtained audio
won’t stand anywhere.

00:53:44.530 --> 00:53:48.500
And these days, everyone knows
AI can fake voices almost perfectly.

00:53:48.780 --> 00:53:52.620
AI or not,
the public already believes it.

00:53:53.100 --> 00:53:54.420
Let’s calm down.

00:53:54.930 --> 00:53:57.420
I still think this government
can move forward.

00:53:59.310 --> 00:54:02.180
We can only move forward
if the public is satisfied.

00:54:03.990 --> 00:54:06.100
Why is everyone panicking?

00:54:06.410 --> 00:54:09.380
I’m telling you,
it’s not as bad as it looks.

00:54:10.110 --> 00:54:13.780
Honestly, Uncle. I think we should
reshuffle a few ministries.

00:54:17.470 --> 00:54:19.340
I think we all agree,

00:54:19.900 --> 00:54:20.860
right, Anuwat?

00:54:21.120 --> 00:54:22.660
I’m for democracy.

00:54:23.050 --> 00:54:25.460
I’ll go with the majority.

00:54:26.540 --> 00:54:29.460
Exactly.
We need to follow people’s will.

00:54:30.130 --> 00:54:33.020
Wiwat Siam had held
the power over the ministries,

00:54:33.180 --> 00:54:34.620
and it hadn’t worked out.

00:54:34.820 --> 00:54:37.980
Maybe it’s time the other
coalition partners took a turn.

00:54:38.500 --> 00:54:39.740
Wouldn’t you agree, Prime Minister?

00:54:42.950 --> 00:54:47.300
In that case, we should call
a full coalition meeting first.

00:54:48.350 --> 00:54:50.340
But really, Uncle,
you could have decided this yourself.

00:54:50.800 --> 00:54:52.060
We’re all family here.

00:54:55.200 --> 00:54:56.540
So, Sun, what do you want?

00:54:58.100 --> 00:55:00.140
Health, like you’ve always said?

00:55:00.670 --> 00:55:03.180
The ministry under Dr. Nong,
even if nobody wants it,

00:55:03.340 --> 00:55:05.100
you’ll have to replace him anyway, right?

00:55:06.310 --> 00:55:07.460
Given where things stand,

00:55:07.570 --> 00:55:11.940
Uncle, you should be listening to
what the rest of us want.

00:55:26.860 --> 00:55:29.540
There’s too much
swirling around you, Doctor.

00:55:32.250 --> 00:55:33.620
I’ll be blunt:

00:55:34.220 --> 00:55:39.540
our party has to
vote no confidence in you.

00:55:51.780 --> 00:55:53.700
Dad, I have a plan. I can handle this.

00:55:55.170 --> 00:55:57.900
You’ve been watching
the numbers too, haven’t you?

00:55:59.170 --> 00:56:03.340
It’s time we show the public
some sincerity.

00:56:05.560 --> 00:56:07.540
Otherwise, this government won’t last.

00:56:07.850 --> 00:56:08.900
Wait, sir.

00:56:09.560 --> 00:56:11.500
If you remove me now,

00:56:13.020 --> 00:56:15.180
there’ll be no one left
actually working for the people.

00:56:15.340 --> 00:56:20.580
That’s not how the public sees it.

00:56:27.770 --> 00:56:30.140
So this is ‘for the people,’ is it?

00:56:30.580 --> 00:56:33.620
Are you removing me for them...

00:56:34.890 --> 00:56:36.300
or for another party?

00:56:36.770 --> 00:56:39.980
Don’t you think that crosses a line?

00:56:47.740 --> 00:56:49.140
No, sir.

00:56:52.430 --> 00:56:53.780
If anything,
I haven’t gone far enough.

00:56:55.220 --> 00:56:57.420
You’re trying to lock in
other parties’ support

00:56:57.580 --> 00:57:00.260
for your own confidence vote.

00:57:00.740 --> 00:57:03.740
If you truly cared about the people,

00:57:03.970 --> 00:57:07.660
trade any other ministry
but not this one.

00:57:11.350 --> 00:57:14.740
You think you’re the only one working?

00:57:17.130 --> 00:57:21.580
Governing means
seeing the big picture,

00:57:22.380 --> 00:57:26.300
the party’s future,
and the government’s.

00:57:32.500 --> 00:57:34.260
We can’t carry that
if we’re busy carrying you.

00:57:36.540 --> 00:57:38.900
I can’t step down now, sir.

00:57:39.810 --> 00:57:41.540
I still have so much to do.

00:57:43.870 --> 00:57:45.100
No, Doctor.

00:57:48.820 --> 00:57:51.140
There’s nothing more you can do.

00:58:09.060 --> 00:58:11.340
If I have to clash with your father...

00:58:14.620 --> 00:58:15.660
what would happen?

00:58:16.450 --> 00:58:19.020
That's an even bigger thought
you must avoid.

00:58:19.530 --> 00:58:23.940
And after the debate, Dr. Nong will
become the first minister in history

00:58:24.220 --> 00:58:26.780
to be removed from office
by a no-confidence vote.

00:58:27.140 --> 00:58:28.300
I'll help the Doctor.

00:58:28.890 --> 00:58:29.700
What do you want?

00:58:29.860 --> 00:58:32.100
I'm certainly not helping
that Doctor for free.

00:58:32.460 --> 00:58:33.300
Who knows?

00:58:33.580 --> 00:58:36.060
This debate round might
turn out to be entertaining.